name: Andreas Karlsson
comment:
This is actually a pretty good school project. The lighting transition at 1.55 was neat but it was just too much, the contrast is just way too obvious and it looks weird. I get what you aimed for, with that nice atmosphere to the environment, but ya, it was just too much, especially when you look at the sun lit areas at 2:20 and 2:55 for example, it looks especially odd.
Also at the beginning the weather and sky was very cloudy, but which suddenly turned into a bright sunny afternoon halfway through the movie. I guess it was hard to get it all in one day or to go back and film another day but with the same cloudy weather, but it looks odd, but understandable.
But yeah, all in all it was a great movie overall! =) Good job Ye Kon!

Nah, just kidding ;) it was really cool. Kudos to you guys.
